[[File:Baruntse wp.jpg|thumb|Mount Baruntse in the Himalayas]] '''Chhewang Nima''' ({{lang-ne|छेवाङ निमा}}) ({{circa}} 1967 – 23 October 2010) was a well known [[Nepalese people|Nepalese]] [[Sherpa people|Sherpa]] who had climbed [[Mount Everest]] 19 times at the time of his loss on Baruntse.<ref name="bbc">{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-south-asia-11615856|title=Leading Sherpa Chhewang Nima missing after avalanche|publisher=BBC News Online|date=24 October 2010|accessdate=24 October 2010}}</ref> He was also called Chuwang Nima,<ref>[http://www.evk2cnr.org/cms/files/evk2cnr.org/24-08-2009_mounteverest.pdf Everest Web - ExWeb special: Himalaya fall season kick-off with a huge spring flashback]</ref> and Chuwang Nima Sherpa.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.cnn.com/2010/WORLD/asiapcf/10/25/nepal.missing.sherpa/|title=Search on for sherpa who has scaled Everest 19 times|last=Shrestha|first=From journalist Manesh|access-date=2017-05-16|language=en}}</ref> His loss in the avalanche and subsequent search made international news, and he was a well known mountaineer in the United States as well as Nepal.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.cnn.com/2010/WORLD/asiapcf/10/25/nepal.missing.sherpa/|title=Search on for sherpa who has scaled Everest 19 times|last=Shrestha|first=From journalist Manesh|access-date=2017-05-16|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-south-asia-11618349|title=Search for missing Nepal Sherpa Chhewang Nima stopped|date=2010-10-25|work=BBC News|access-date=2017-05-16|language=en-GB}}</ref> He worked as a professional mountaineer, but at the time of his loss he was helping another team fix lines after they had asked for help.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.cnn.com/2010/WORLD/asiapcf/10/25/nepal.missing.sherpa/|title=Search on for sherpa who has scaled Everest 19 times|last=Shrestha|first=From journalist Manesh|access-date=2017-05-16|language=en}}</ref>
His disappearance, after being struck by an [[avalanche]] near the summit of [[Baruntse|Mount Baruntse]], was reported on 24 October 2010.<ref name="bbc"/> On 25 October it was announced that the search had been called off.<ref>[https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-south-asia-11618349 BBC News: Search for missing Nepal Sherpa Chhewang Nima stopped]</ref>
Examples of summits: ;Everest *May 19, 1998<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.everestsummiteersassociation.org/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=13:nepal&limitstart=3|title=Nepal|last=Sherpa|first=Sherap|website=www.everestsummiteersassociation.org|language=en-gb|access-date=2017-05-16}}</ref> *May 20, 2006 Chuwang Nima Sherpa (Tesho, Nepal)<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.himalayandatabase.com/2006%20Season%20Lists/2006%20Spring%20A12.html|title=Himalayan Database Expedition Archives of Elizabeth Hawley|website=www.himalayandatabase.com|access-date=2017-05-16}}</ref> ;Ama Dablam *October 26, 2009 Chuwang Nima Sherpa (Tesho, Nepal)<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.himalayandatabase.com/2009%20Season%20Lists/2009%20Autumn%20A1.html|title=Himalayan Database Expedition Archives of Elizabeth Hawley|website=www.himalayandatabase.com|access-date=2017-05-16}}</ref>
At the time of Chhewang's loss he had 19 Everest summits, one short of most in the World, [[Apa Sherpa]]'s who had 20 ascents at the time of Chhewang's loss.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.cnn.com/2010/WORLD/asiapcf/10/25/nepal.missing.sherpa/|title=Search on for sherpa who has scaled Everest 19 times|last=Shrestha|first=From journalist Manesh|access-date=2017-05-16|language=en}}</ref> (Apa later increased this to 21) ==See also== *[[List of Mount Everest summiters by number of times to the summit]] *[[List of 20th-century summiters of Mount Everest]]
