{{Infobox certification mark | name = India Organic | image = [[File:India organic.jpg|180px]] | caption = The 'India Organic' certification mark. | expansion = | agency = APEDA | region = | founded = 2002 | defunct = | predecessor = | successor = | products = [[Organic food]] | type = | legalstatus = Advisory | mandatorysince = | homepage = }}
'''India Organic''' is a [[Organic certification|certification mark for organically farmed food]] products manufactured in India.<ref>[http://www.indianspices.com/html/np_organiccert.htm Spices Board of India. 'Organic certification mark'.] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120802024444/http://www.indianspices.com/html/np_organiccert.htm |date=August 2, 2012 }}</ref> The [[certification mark]] certifies that an [[organic food]] product conforms to the National Standards for Organic Products<ref>[http://apeda.gov.in/apedawebsite/organic/ORGANIC_CONTENTS/National_Programme_for_Organic_Production.htm APEDA. 'National Standards for Organic Products.']</ref> established in 2000.
Those standards ensures that the product or the raw materials used in the product were grown through [[organic farming]], without the use of chemical [[fertilizer]]s, [[pesticide]]s, or induced hormones. The certification is issued by testing centres accredited by the Agricultural and Processed Food Products Export Development Authority (APEDA).<ref>[http://www.apeda.gov.in/apedawebsite/organic/Organic_Products.htm Agricultural and Processed Food Products Export Development Authority. 'Organic products'.]</ref> under the ''National Program for Organic Production'' of the [[Government of India]].<ref name="ecoworld">[http://www.ecoworld.com/atmosphere/effects/organic-farming-in-india.html Ecoworld. Organic Farming in India.]</ref><ref>[http://www.nabard.org/fileupload/databank/occasionalpapers/oc%2038.pdf Nabard. Paper on organic farming.]</ref>
Even though the standards are in effect since 2000, the certification scheme and hence the certification mark came into existence in 2002.<ref name="ecoworld" />
