'''Mary Grant''' (6 August 1928 – 18 September 2016)<ref name="death">{{Cite web |url=http://www.ghanaweb.com/GhanaHomePage/NewsArchive/Former-member-of-Council-of-State-Dr-Mary-Grant-dead-at-88-470659 |title=Former member of Council of State Dr. Mary Grant is dead |accessdate=19 September 2016 |work=GhanaWeb |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160920131639/http://www.ghanaweb.com/GhanaHomePage/NewsArchive/Former-member-of-Council-of-State-Dr-Mary-Grant-dead-at-88-470659 |archive-date=2016-09-20 |dead-url=no |df= }}</ref> was a [[Ghanaian]] physician and politician. She was [[Ghana]]'s first [[Council of State (Ghana)|Council of State]] member and also the first [[Wesley Girls' Senior High School|Wesley Girls High School]] alumna to be a medical doctor.<ref name=WG>{{cite web|title=Achievement of Past Students|url=http://wesleygirls.edu.gh/achievement/past-students|website=Wesley Girls High School|accessdate=5 September 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160901050238/http://wesleygirls.edu.gh/achievement/past-students|archive-date=2016-09-01|dead-url=no|df=}}</ref> She was a distant relation of [[Paa Grant]], who has been called ''"the father of Gold Coast politics".<ref>Jonas Nyabor, [http://newscentral.exsees.com/item/149108a86350795db9b73694893b2c9e-4e7ee1f43e16a00a2678f2d8f54a2df3 "Mary Grant was 'a formidable woman' – Rawlings"] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170107005230/http://newscentral.exsees.com/item/149108a86350795db9b73694893b2c9e-4e7ee1f43e16a00a2678f2d8f54a2df3 |date=2017-01-07 }}, ''News Central'', Citifmonline, 29 September 2016.</ref>''
==Education == Mary Grant had her secondary education from the Wesley Girls High School in [[Cape Coast]],<ref name=WG /> and went on to become the school's first alumna to qualify as a medical doctor after completing her training in the [[United Kingdom]].<ref name=funeral>Delali Adogla-Bessa, [http://newscentral.exsees.com/item/149108a86350795db9b73694893b2c9e-000410ba9a7c6cde4197760341ecee81 "Rawlings, Kufuor, Mahama, pay last respects to Mary Grant"] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170107004429/http://newscentral.exsees.com/item/149108a86350795db9b73694893b2c9e-000410ba9a7c6cde4197760341ecee81 |date=2017-01-07 }}, ''News Central'', Citifmonline, 21 October 2016.</ref>
==Career== Mary Grant began her political career when she appointed Secretary of Health in 1985.<ref>{{cite web|title=Former member of Council of State Dr Mary Grant dies at 88|url=http://www.myjoyonline.com/news/2016/September-18th/dr-mary-grant-has-died-at-88.php|website=Myjoyonline|publisher=Myjoyonline|accessdate=4 March 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170105095400/http://www.myjoyonline.com/news/2016/September-18th/dr-mary-grant-has-died-at-88.php|archive-date=2017-01-05|dead-url=no|df=}}</ref> Grant held many positions, including Deputy Minister of Health and Member of the [[Provisional National Defense Council]] (PNDC). She later became the Minister of Education and Culture and also a Member of Council of State.<ref>{{cite web|title=Ghana: Mary Grant Against Marriage At 16|url=http://allafrica.com/stories/199806180171.html|work=The Independent (Accra)|publisher=allAfrica|date=18 June 1998|accessdate=5 September 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Kofi|first1=Yeboah|title=Cases of high blood pressure, diabetes go up - Pobee|url=http://kofiyebo.blogspot.com/2007/11/cases-of-high-blood-pressure-diabetes.html|website=Kofi Yeboah Stories|date=12 November 2007|accessdate=5 September 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161013190328/http://kofiyebo.blogspot.com/2007/11/cases-of-high-blood-pressure-diabetes.html|archive-date=2016-10-13|dead-url=no|df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=FRIMPONG-BOATENG COUNTS ON RAWLINGS PV OBENG, MARY GRANT… As Unique Trust boss endorses him|url=https://www.modernghana.com/news/124478/frimpong-boateng-counts-on-rawlings-pv-obeng-mary-grant-as.html|website=Modern Ghana|publisher=Ghanaian Chronicle|date=23 February 2007|accessdate=5 September 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170107100204/https://www.modernghana.com/news/124478/frimpong-boateng-counts-on-rawlings-pv-obeng-mary-grant-as.html|archive-date=2017-01-07|dead-url=no|df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Mrs. Grant Launches Millennium Excellence Awards|url=http://www.ghanaweb.com/GhanaHomePage/economy/artikel.php?ID=8394|website=GhanaWeb|date=26 August 1999|accessdate=5 September 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160919011422/http://www.ghanaweb.com/GhanaHomePage/economy/artikel.php?ID=8394|archive-date=2016-09-19|dead-url=no|df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=The late President Mills buried|url=http://ghananewsagency.org/social/the-late-president-mills-buried-47588|website=Ghana News Agency|publisher=Ghana News Agency|accessdate=5 September 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160916225217/http://ghananewsagency.org/social/the-late-president-mills-buried-47588|archive-date=2016-09-16|dead-url=no|df=}}</ref>
She led Ghana's delegation to many international conferences, including [[World Health Organization|World Health Organisation]] (WHO) General Assemblies in [[Geneva]] and Regional Conferences in Africa, [[World Bank]] Meeting in Africa Health, Cairo Conference on Population and Development, and she was among Ghanas delegation to the Beijing Conference on Women's Rights.<ref name=joyonline />
==Awards and honours== Grant received an award during the Maiden Women's Award ceremony.<ref>{{cite web|title=Supporting quality healthcare and community projects, Saboba, Ghana|url=http://www.sabobashope.net/award.html|website=Saboba's Hope, Inc.|publisher=Saboba's Hope Fullerton, Ca|accessdate=5 September 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160911133107/http://www.sabobashope.net/award.html|archive-date=2016-09-11|dead-url=no|df=}}</ref>
== Death == She died aged 88, on the afternoon of 18 September 2016 at the [[37 Military Hospital]] in [[Accra]],<ref name=joyonline>{{Cite web|url=http://www.myjoyonline.com/news/2016/September-18th/dr-mary-grant-has-died-at-88.php|title=Ghana News - Former member of Council of State Dr Mary Grant dies at 88|last=|website=Myjoyonline.com|date=19 September 2016|accessdate=20 September 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160920124531/http://www.myjoyonline.com/news/2016/September-18th/dr-mary-grant-has-died-at-88.php|archive-date=2016-09-20|dead-url=no|df=}}</ref> and was given a [[state funeral]].<ref name=funeral />
